    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="862"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d862">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Riddle</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 580.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram<note n="b" xml:id="d862fnb">Printed, <ref target="#pg_6">page
                            6</ref>.</note> of May 24.</p>
                <p>I inclose herewith the reply of the Russian Government to my request made in
                    accordance with your instructions.</p>
                <p>I have communicated the substance of this note to the consul-general in this
                    city, instructing him to inform all the consular representatives under him.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. W. Riddle</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad Interim.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Prince <persName type="from">Obolensky</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Riddle</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry for Foreign Affairs</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1902</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Chargé d’affaires</hi>: In reply to your note of
                        May 13 (26), I have the honor to inform you that the Imperial Government
                        sees no objection to the interests of Cuba and its citizens being
                        represented by consular officers of the United States residing in Russia, as
                        requested by the President of the Republic of Cuba.</p>
                    <p>Please receive, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Obolensky.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
